## Backend for Frontend (BFF) Pattern

Different clients have different needs — a mobile app needs smaller payloads, a web app needs richer data. The BFF pattern creates a **dedicated gateway per client type**:

```
Mobile BFF     → optimized for mobile: small payloads, offline support
Web BFF        → optimized for web: richer data, server-side aggregation
Partner BFF    → rate limited, versioned, API-key authenticated
Admin BFF      → wider access, internal tooling
```

```java
// BFF aggregates multiple service calls for mobile
@GetMapping("/mobile/home")
public MobileHomePage getHome(Authentication auth) {
    // Fan-out in parallel
    CompletableFuture<UserSummary> user = userService.getSummaryAsync(auth.getName());
    CompletableFuture<List<OrderSummary>> orders = orderService.getRecentAsync(auth.getName());
    CompletableFuture<List<ProductSummary>> products = productService.getFeaturedAsync();

    // Wait for all and compose response
    return MobileHomePage.of(
        user.join(),
        orders.join(),
        products.join()
    );
    // One request from mobile → 3 parallel service calls
}
```
